    "Background": {
      "text": "Also known as late post-MI pericarditis\nPericarditis\nthat occurs one week to several months after a myocardial infarction\nThought to be immunologic and is less commonly seen after\nPE\n,\npericardial trauma\n, or pericardiectomy.\n[1]",
